    <S id="022S2">
        <FORM kindOf="original">saka "qadjaw tu ki namatsemu anga a ku siniqadjay," nu aya ti Salakats, qau pavalitan a siniqadjay, aya.</FORM>
        <PHON kindOf="original">saka "qaɉaw tu ki namaʦəmu aŋa a ku siniqaɉaj," nu aja ti saɭakaʦ, qau pavaɭitan a siniqaɉaj, aja.</PHON>
        <FORM kindOf="standard">saka "qadjaw tu ki namacemu anga a ku siniqadjay," nu aya ti Salakac, qau pavalitan a siniqadjay, aya.</FORM>
        <PHON kindOf="standard">saka "qaɉaw tu ki namaʦəmu aŋa a ku siniqaɉaj," nu aja ti saɣakaʦ, qau pavaɣitan a siniqaɉaj, aja.</PHON>
        <TRANSL xml:lang="en">So when Salakats thinks: “I wonder if the ties have rotted,” then the ties are changed, they say.</TRANSL>
